library(broom)

clustered_edu %>% 
  tidy(col.names = colnames(edu_scale))

withinss (within sum of squares) = average distance between points in that cluster we want to have a small withinss

add cluster group to original data set

clustered_edu %>% 
  augment(edu_data)
glance(clustered_edu)

tot.withinss (total within sum of squares) = sum(withinss)

# set min & max number of clusters
max_k <- 20

k_clusters <- tibble(
  k = 1:max_k
)

k_clusters <- k_clusters %>% 
  mutate(
    kclust = map(k, ~ kmeans(edu_scale, .x, nstart = 25)), # .x represents "k" 
    tidied = map(kclust, tidy),
    glanced = map(kclust, glance),
    augmented = map(kclust, augment, edu_data)
  )
clusterings <- k_clusters %>% 
  unnest(glanced)

clusterings

elbow chart

clusterings %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = k,
             y = tot.withinss))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_line()+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(1, 20 , 1))

library(factoextra)

fviz_nbclust(edu_scale,
             kmeans,
             method = "wss",
             nstart = 25)

silhouetting

fviz_nbclust(edu_scale,
             kmeans,
             method = "silhouette",
             nstart = 25)

fviz_nbclust(edu_scale,
             kmeans,
             method = "gap_stat",
             nstart = 25)
